## 🧠 PART 3 — Tech Stack Deep Dive

### 3.1 SQL Server

> [!info] What it is
> Microsoft SQL Server — an enterprise relational database. Used in many traditional enterprises (ITC included) for transactional data.

**Why used in this project:**
- ITC's existing infrastructure used SQL Server
- Structured event data (timestamps, severity, plant ID, machine ID) fits well in SQL
- Strong query capabilities for filtering and aggregation
- Integration with Grafana via SQL plugin

**Key SQL operations used:**
- INSERT — logging events
- SELECT with filters, GROUP BY for dashboards
- Indexed columns for fast lookups (timestamp, plant_id, severity)
- Views for role-based access control

**Interview prep:**
- *"Why SQL Server over PostgreSQL?"* → ITC's existing infrastructure used SQL Server; chose to integrate rather than introduce another DB
- *"Why a SQL database for logs?"* → Structured event data fits SQL well. Time-series databases would be better for high-volume metrics, but the volume here was manageable

