### 3.2 Grafana

> [!info] What it is
> Grafana is an open-source dashboard and visualization platform. Connects to many data sources (Prometheus, Loki, SQL databases, etc.) and renders interactive dashboards.

**Why Grafana:**
- Industry standard for observability dashboards
- Supports many data sources
- Powerful query and visualization options
- Role-based access control
- Alerting built-in
- Plugin ecosystem

**What you built in Grafana:**

**Role-based dashboards:**
- Plant Engineer view: server health, error logs, critical events, plant-specific
- Manager view: KPI summaries, trends, multi-plant comparison

**Plant-specific filters:**
- Variable in dashboard (`$plant`) that users select
- All queries filter on the selected plant
- Single dashboard, multiple plant views

**Alert mechanisms:**
- Alerts on error rate spikes
- Alerts on critical event keywords
- Notification channels (email, Slack)

**Interview prep:**
- *"Why Grafana?"* → Industry standard, supports many data sources, role-based access, alerting built-in
- *"How did you implement role-based dashboards?"* → Multiple dashboards, each with permission scoping. Plant engineers see operational details; managers see KPIs and trends
- *"How did you do plant-specific filtering?"* → Dashboard variables — a `$plant` dropdown that drives all panel queries

